[1
Date: Thu, 26 Oct 2000 11:36:46 GMT
From: M. Cosgriff <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Khaleej Times Online, AFP Report, 26 Oct 2000 [edited
<http://www.khaleejtimes.com/middleeast.htm>

Rift Valley Fever Death Toll Rises In Saudi Arabia & Yemen
-----------------------------------------------------------
RIYADH - The number of Saudi dead from Rift Valley Fever, which struck the
Saudi-Yemen border area in early September, has climbed to 88 the Health
Ministry said yesterday. "Three more deaths have been recorded in the Saudi
Kingdom [since the last report on Tue 23 Oct 2000," said a statement
released in Riyadh. The Ministry said 450 people have contracted the virus
[compared with the figure of 443 given on 23 Oct 2000, but 346 have been
able to leave hospital after recovering.
The virus has also struck neighbouring Yemen, where a statement from the
Health And Agriculture Ministries said "97 people have died and 1797
animals have perished". [This compares with a figure of 71 deaths quoted in
a report in The Times of India on Tue 24 Oct 2000. - Mod.CP The 2 Yemeni
Ministries have urged the World Health Organisation and the United Nations
Food and Agriculture Organisation to help Yemen fend off this epidemic. The
World Health Organisation has launched an appeal for $975 000 to help boost
international efforts to counter the disease in Yemen.
